<HEAD>17 Drown In Ferry Sinking</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 At least 17 people drowned when a small ferry boat sank off <LOCATION> Luzon </LOCATION> island on the same day that 55 people were killed in a similar sinking in the central <LOCATION> Philippines </LOCATION>, the Philippine Constabulary reported today. A belated report said five other people were missing from the <LOCATION> Lady </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Aurea </LOCATION>, a motorized outrigger which capsized as it was buffeted by big waves Friday off <LOCATION> Aurora </LOCATION> province, 120 miles northeast of <LOCATION> Manila </LOCATION>. It said 11 others were rescued. The report gave no other details. At least 55 people drowned and 77 others were rescued when an overloaded ferry boat sank during a squall Friday as it was sailing from <LOCATION> Samar </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> Leyte </LOCATION> island in the central <LOCATION> Philippines </LOCATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> reported last Saturday.
