<HEAD>AIDS Victims' Sperm Is Free Of Virus</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS 2nd graf to add full name of school.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Men with the AIDS virus have AIDS-free sperm, raising the possibility that infected males may be able to father children through artificial insemination without passing the disease to the fetus, researchers say. Dr. <PERSON> Bernard </PERSON> <PERSON> Poiesz </PERSON> and colleagues at the <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Health </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Science </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> at <LOCATION> Syracuse </LOCATION> found that the AIDS virus is present in the seminal fluid in which the sperm is suspended but not in the sperm cells themselves, <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION> reported today. <PERSON> Poiesz </PERSON> and researchers at the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Southern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION> working independently found that most men with AIDS do not even have the virus in their semen, the Times said. Researchers are baffled by this finding because theoretically, if AIDS is present in the blood, it should be present in semen, since that fluid contains the white cells that the virus attacks. Poiesz reported the virus is present in about 20 percent of the semen samples of infected men, while the virus is present in virtually 100 percent of their blood samples. In contrast, several years ago <PERSON> Poiesz </PERSON> detected AIDS in 70 percent of semen samples from infected men. Dr. <PERSON> Suraiya </PERSON> <PERSON> Rasheed </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> USC </ORGANIZATION> also reported that researchers in her laboratory were no longer able to detect the AIDS virus in most semen samples from men whose blood samples show an infection rate of virtually 100 percent.
