<HEAD>State To Seek Continued Custody Of Children</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOE SCHULA</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>OREGON CITY, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Fifty-nine children found crowded in a four-bedroom farmhouse should remain in state custody while authorities investigate the beating death of an 8-year-old girl, officials said. Four people have been charged with murder in the death of <PERSON> Dayna </PERSON> <PERSON> Lorea </PERSON> <PERSON> Broussard </PERSON>, the daughter of the founder of a Los Angeles-based Christian center established to train and discipline inner-city youngsters. <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Coleman </PERSON>, chief deputy state medical examiner, said Sunday the girl had been `` whipped severely'' and suffered fatal `` blunt-force injuries.'' There also was evidence of an old injury on her body, <PERSON> Coleman </PERSON> said. Police said several adults from the rural home near <LOCATION> Sandy </LOCATION>, which once served as the headquarters for the now-defunct <ORGANIZATION> Ecclesia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Athletic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION>, brought the dead child to a fire station 25 miles east of <LOCATION> Portland </LOCATION> early Friday. Investigators later found the other children in the four-bedroom farmhouse, some with scars that might indicate physical abuse, said sheriff's Capt. <PERSON> Pat </PERSON> <PERSON> Detloff </PERSON>. The children, ranging in age from 1 -LCB- months to 16 years, were hungry but otherwise healthy, according to officials who admitted them to state juvenile facilities over the weekend. All reportedly were from <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>. `` Based on everything we know right now, we'll recommend continued -LRB- state -RRB- custody,'' said <PERSON> Bart </PERSON> <PERSON> Wilson </PERSON>, a branch manager of the state Children's Services Division. The division planned to ask authorities to approve the custody extension at a juvenile court hearing in <LOCATION> Oregon </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> this afternoon. `` We've had little contact with the parents,'' <P