<HEAD>Student Dies After Crashing Through Skylight</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Rabsary is cq</NOTE>
<DATELINE>HIALEAH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A 16-year-old girl who crashed through a skylight while taking yearbook pictures on the roof of her high school has died after two days in a coma, authorities said. <PERSON> Rabsary </PERSON> <PERSON> Gutierrez </PERSON>, a junior at Hialeah-Miami Lakes High, dropped 30 feet on Friday when she apparently misjudged her step and plunged through the glass skylight onto a concrete stairway, suffering head, brain and lung injuries. She never regained consciousness and died Sunday at <ORGANIZATION> Jackson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Memorial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hospital </ORGANIZATION>, said <PERSON> Principal </PERSON> <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Noble </PERSON>. `` She was a real sweet person whom everybody cared about,'' he said. `` This has been real difficult for all of us who knew her.'' Special counselors came to the school today to help students deal with the tragedy, he said. Miss <PERSON> Gutierrez </PERSON> had just taken a picture on top of the three-story building when she tried to step over the skylight. Instead, she crashed through as a teacher and 24 students looked on, police Lt. <PERSON> Lowell </PERSON> <PERSON> Coffin </PERSON> said. The students had been warned to walk around the skylight, and students had gone on the roof previously to take pictures without incident, officials said.
