rd a car he had driven to the scene, officials said. Mrs. <PERSON> Bloomberg </PERSON> `` just sat down on the sidewalk, pretending her legs had collapsed under her,'' Mrs. <PERSON> Liberace </PERSON> said. `` He tried to lift her in the car but could n't. He leaned back for a minute and the police shot him.'' `` When I sat down I figured the police would pick him off, maybe,'' Mrs. <PERSON> Bloomberg </PERSON> said. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Sullivan </PERSON>, deputy chief of detectives, said the man threatened Mrs. <PERSON> Bloomberg </PERSON> `` and she started to resist while he tried to force her into a car.'' She fell to the ground and an officer shot <PERSON> Perry </PERSON> with one bullet, <PERSON> Sullivan </PERSON> said.
