ief sponsor of the <ORGANIZATION> senate </ORGANIZATION>'s anti-nuclear weapons bill, said financial compensation was not the only issue. `` I do n't think it is enough to settle the issue of compensation if the threat of national destruction due to nuclear weapons and the derogation of national sovereignty is still there,'' he said. Left-wing groups pressing for the dismantling of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> facilities branded the agreement a `` sell-out'' and said <PERSON> Manglapus </PERSON> should not have linked continued <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> presence here to the debt issue.
