trollers' union denied there was a misunderstanding. Asked about <PERSON> Chiucini </PERSON>'s remarks, <PERSON> Di </PERSON> <PERSON> Giulio </PERSON> said the tapes of cockpit conversation had yet to be reviewed. Since Sunday evening, a heavy fog had enveloped the <LOCATION> Rome </LOCATION> seacoast including the airport. `` The fog appears to have been the main culprit,'' Di <PERSON> Giulio </PERSON> said. Without citing its sources, RAI state television said the pilot began the third attempt too low. <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> ANSA </ORGANIZATION> news agency said the pilot had approached from three different directions because of shifting fog banks. <PERSON> Andrea </PERSON> <PERSON> Gariup </PERSON>, of <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION>'s main pilots' union, was quoted by RAI as saying the runway on which the pilot tried to land lacked sophisticated equipment to help in instrument landings and was not normally used. Authorities reported both the flight instrument data recordings and the recordings of conversations between cockpit and tower were recovered. <PERSON> Gait </PERSON> said he was involved in a charity project to provide <LOCATION> Uganda </LOCATION> farmers with cows. He told The <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> in an interview at <ORGANIZATION> Sant </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> ` </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Eugenio </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hospital </ORGANIZATION> that he heard the planes' wheels come up, go down and then go up again moments before `` The flames came through the cabin, my wife says. I do n't remember ... We jumped out of a hole in the fuselage behind us.. <PERSON> Ruth </PERSON> jumped backward, holding -LRB- baby <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> -RRB- to her chest and then fell about six feet to the ground I picked them up. We walked about 200 yards and then some Ugandans came out.'' The three Gaits were expected to be discharged by Wednesday.
