<HEAD>Corning Glass Reports Record 3rd-Quarter Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CORNING, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Corning Glass Works more than doubled its net income in the third quarter to a record $ 123.9 million from $ 50 million during the same period last year, the company said Monday. Corning Chairman <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Houghton </PERSON> said `` the excellent results came from equity companies as well as strength across the board in virtually all <PERSON> Corning </PERSON> businesses, where the rate of profitability was the best we've seen for a third quarter in the last decade.'' Even without one-time gains of $ 59 million stemming from transactions in <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>, the third-quarter results were a company record. On a per-share basis, <PERSON> Corning </PERSON> returned $ 2.74 compared to $ 1.08 a year ago. Sales for quarter totaled $ 625.4 million, up 2.5 percent from $ 610.1 million in the same period a year ago. The company said the figure was up 11 percent if adjusted for the disposition of the electronics business in 1987. For the 40 weeks ended Oct. 9, the company reported net income of $ 243 million, up from $ 148.5 million, and sales of $ 1.58 billion, up from $ 1.54 billion. <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Ryan </PERSON>, analyst for <ORGANIZATION> Merrill </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lynch </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, said <PERSON> Corning </PERSON>'s restructuring efforts during the past few years have paid off. The glass maker based in upstate <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> has focused its research and development in four main areas _ fiber optics and telecommunications; medical diagnostic services; ceramics and specialty glasses; and household products. Optical fiber sales were modestly improved, according to <PERSON> Stephen </PERSON> <PERSON> Albertalli </PERSON>, a Corning vice president. `` We projected a flat year in the volatile fiber optics market,'' <PERSON> Albertalli </PERSON> said. `` We're doing a little better than we expected.'' The company's clinical testing service subsidiary, MedPath, <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, expanded exports to Latin American and <LOCATION> Asia </LOCATION> and was part of the reason for a 31 percent increase in income from equity companies. A new manufacturing facility being built by <PERSON> Corning </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Asahi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Glass </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Osooka </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> is expected to expand <PERSON> Corning </PERSON>'s presence in the world market for specialty glass. The plant, which is due to open in 1989, will manufacture glass used in the display modules of portable computers and other electronic devices. The companies household products unit, which manufactures Corning Glassware, also showed strong sales gains.
