ORGANIZATION> said its earnings rose 28.1 percent to $ 462.6 million, or $ 2.22 per fully diluted share, from $ 361.1 million, or $ 1.84 a fully diluted share, a year earlier. Revenue rose 1.6 percent to $ 7.03 billion from $ 6.91 billion. <ORGANIZATION> NCR </ORGANIZATION>, based in <LOCATION> Dayton </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION>, said its revenue and earnings were a record for a third quarter. Earnings rose to $ 103.1 million, or $ 1.26 a share, from $ 97.8 million, or $ 1.05 a share, a year earlier. Revenue rose to $ 1.41 billion from $ 1.34 billion. For the nine months, profit rose 12.3 percent to $ 289.7 million, or $ 3.49 a share, from $ 257.9 million, or $ 2.74 a share, a year earlier. Revenue to $ 4.19 billion from $ 3.82 billion. <ORGANIZATION> Lotus </ORGANIZATION>, of <LOCATION> Cambridge </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mass. </LOCATION>, said it took a charge against its earnings to reflect the costs it will incur when it gives free upgrades to its upcoming version of Lotus 1-2-3 to the people who purchased existing versions under a special promotion. <ORGANIZATION> Lotus </ORGANIZATION>, which repeatedly has postponed introduction of the new software, said it earned $ 14.3 million in the quarter ended Oct. 1, or 31 cents a share, down from $ 19.1 million, or 42 cents a share, a year earlier. Sales rose to $ 116.8 million, from $ 101.2 million. For the first nine months of its fiscal year, <ORGANIZATION> Lotus </ORGANIZATION> said its profit rose to $ 49.9 million, or $ 1.08 a share, from $ 49.1 million, also $ 1.08 a share, a year earlier. Revenue rose to $ 356.2 million, from $ 280 million.
